snippet.textDisplay:
Don't know whether this will be read by Elayna and Riley, but I just felt like sharing this.
I've been following this channel for quite some time. Since their first Atlantic crossing 5 years ago to be exact (I was 15 then).
I don't remember ever leaving a comment under their videos, I just enjoyed following their journey silently from the sideline.
The reason I write this now is because I want to share my fair share of respect towards Elayna and Riley.

It's hugely inspiring to see the amount of dedication they have put in all they have been doing. Consistently sharing these videos despite the difficulties they experienced. The effort put in improving the quality they share (I love seeing the differences in quality between Ep.1 and now). The dedication to keep up this (sometimes) challenging and adventurous lifestyle. Creating a tight community and using this community for good causes. And of course, being amazing parents for little Lenny.

I have been sailing since 2011 and loved it ever since. Despite how amazing I think a lifestyle sailing around the world would be, I know that it's not a lifestyle suited for me. That's why it's been such a pleasure to feel like I'm part of this lifestyle through Elayna and Riley.
You guys helped me give happiness in times when I needed it.
I wish the best of luck to you three, hopefully with many many more years living the life you most enjoy.


Thank you for everything,
Robbe

snippet.textDisplay:
The Gospel of Jesus Christ
Evil is Temporary
The Good News of Jesus Christ proclaims that all evil in the world today is a temporary situation. The Bible teaches that one day the risen Jesus Christ will return to earth and establish His Kingdom of Love, Righteousness, and Peace on Earth. He came here to die for our sins and purchase with his blood a place in heaven for us. He offers the gift of eternal life to anyone who will trust in him as Lord and Savior.
God Created Man in His Image
The Bible begins with God creating everything. Then He creates man. Genesis 1:26 And God said, "Let Us make man in Our image, after our likeness: and let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over the fowl of the air, and over the cattle and over ever creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth." God gave us the supreme compliment of creating us in his image. Nothing else in God's creation is in His image except mankind.
The Holy Trinity
The Hebrew word for God is Elohim. Elohim is a plural noun used in grammatical agreement with a singular verb "bara" meaning created. This is our first glimpse into the Godhead. The Holy Trinity of God consists of God the Father, God the Son(Word), and God the Holy Spirit (sometimes he is referred to as Holy Ghost). They are 3 distinct persons of majesty and glory but only 1 God. 1John 5:7 "For there are three that bear record in Heaven, The Father, The Word, and the Holy Ghost and these three are one." Mark 12:29 "And Jesus answered him, The first of all the commandments is, Hear, O Israel: The Lord our God is one Lord."
My best analogy to understand this is - if you take my physical father here on earth he is James Brown the Father, James Brown the son, and James Brown the husband. We have three distinct persons in relationships but only 1 man. So we have the Godhead of three distinct persons of Holiness and Majesty, God the Father, God the Son, and God the Holy Spirit.
Originally man was created with a state of sinlessness and moral likeness to God. When man sinned he lost that moral likeness although he retained his will, and the natural likeness of emotions and intellect.
Fall of Mankind brought Death and Separation from God
Adam the first man was created to live forever. However when he disobeyed God he brought physical death and spiritual death on himself and all of mankind. God had commanded both Adam and Eve the first woman not to eat of the tree of knowledge of good and evil warning them that for in that day they would die. Genesis 2:17 "But of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil thou shalt not eat, for in that day that thou eatest thereof thou shalt surely die." The serpent Satan, deceived Eve, and they both did eat.
Romans 5:12 "Therefore just as through one man sin entered in the world and death through sin, and so death spread to all men, because all have sinned."
Mankind's Desperate Situation
That left all of mankind in a desperate situation. Fallen mankind not only inherited physical death but was spiritually separated from their Loving, Just, Holy, Creator. God's wrath is directed against all ungodliness and evil and the Bible says one day there will be a Great Judgment and because God is Just He must and will punish all sin. The Bible says that God will not be mocked but every man, woman, and child will give an account of themselves on judgment day.
Good News-God has a Plan of Salvation
The Gospel of Jesus Christ is the most beautiful Love Story of all time. The Gospels of the Bible show a Loving & Forgiving Creator who comes to save the world from eternal damnation.
The Bible says, "God so Loved the World that He gave His only begotten Son, so that whosoever believes in Him should not perish but have everlasting life."
Who is God's Son Jesus Christ?
John 1:1 "In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
John 1:2 "The same was in the beginning with God.
John 1:3 "All things were made by Him: and without Him was not anything made that was made." Jesus made everything.
John 1:4 "In Him was life: and the life was the light of men."
John 1:5 "And the light shineth in the darkness; and the darkness comprehended it not."
John 1:14 "And the Word was made Flesh, and dwelt among us (and we beheld His Glory, from the Glory of the only begotten from the Father) full of Grace and Truth." Emanuel means God with Us.
The Reason for God becoming Flesh
For by Grace (God's goodness) are ye saved, through FAITH and not by your own means, lest anybody boasts.
Jesus came to save the world because man could not save himself. Our jealous creator Loves us.
How do we obtain Faith?
Romans 10:17 "So then Faith cometh by hearing, and hearing by the Word of God." Every man is given a measure of faith.
Kenosis of Christ
Kenosis is a Greek word meaning literally to empty out. The true doctrine of the Kenosis of Christ involves a veiling of His preincarnate glory and voluntary waiving of some His divine prerogatives during the time He was on earth. The Kenosis of Christ during His incarnation does not mean He surrendered any attributes of deity but He took on the limitations of mankind. It was condension in taking the likeness of sinful flesh in this incarnation. He was fully man and fully God.
Philippians 2:6-10
2:6 "Who being in the form of God, thought it not robbery, to be equal to God (God the Father)."
2:7 "But made Himself no reputation, took upon Him the form of a servant, and was made in the likeness of men: (flesh)."
2:8 "And being fashioned as a man, He humbled Himself and became obedient unto Death, even the death of the Cross. (Who was he obedient to? God the Father, who sent the Son to die on the Cross for all of mankind's sin.")
2:9 "And wherefore God hath highly exalted Him, and given Him a name which is above every name."
2:10 "That at the name of Jesus every knee should bow of things in Heaven and things in Earth, and things under the earth:
2:11 "And that every tongue should confess, that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the Glory of God the Father. (When we confess that Jesus Christ is Lord it is to the Glory of God the Father because He is the one that sent Him.)"
John 3:16 "For God so loved the world that He gave His only begotten Son, so that whosoever believe in Him should not perish but have everlasting life."

The Reason for God becoming Flesh
For by Grace (God's goodness) are ye saved, through FAITH and not by your own means, lest anybody boasts.
Jesus came to save the world because man could not save himself. Our jealous creator Loves us.
How do we obtain Faith?
Romans 10:17 "So then Faith cometh by hearing, and hearing by the Word of God." Every man is given a measure of faith.
Kenosis of Christ
Kenosis is a Greek word meaning literally to empty out. The true doctrine of the Kenosis of Christ involves a veiling of His preincarnate glory and voluntary waiving of some His divine prerogatives during the time He was on earth. The Kenosis of Christ during His incarnation does not mean He surrendered any attributes of deity but He took on the limitations of mankind. It was condension in taking the likeness of sinful flesh in this incarnation. He was fully man and fully God.
Philippians 2:6-10
2:6 "Who being in the form of God, thought it not robbery, to be equal to God (God the Father)."
2:7 "But made Himself no reputation, took upon Him the form of a servant, and was made in the likeness of men: (flesh)."

2:9 "And wherefore God hath highly exalted Him, and given Him a name which is above every name."
2:10 "That at the name of Jesus every knee should bow of things in Heaven and things in Earth, and things under the earth:
2:11 "And that every tongue should confess, that Jesus Christ is Lord, to the Glory of God the Father. (When we confess that Jesus Christ is Lord it is to the Glory of God the Father because He is the one that sent Him.)"

snippet.textDisplay: Newport is home for us in the summer, such an amazing place.  Great to see you guys when you were there.  Sorry we never connected for dinner.  Hope all is well.  To answer your question on how long to stay.. I think it is a bit of a formula..  usually it takes a few days to sync with the speed of a place, get acclimated and forget about the last place you were.  Then I think you stay double that to get to know the culture and the locals.  IF it is a tourist destination, you have to add a few days for the must see to tourist stuff, but that usually isn't our thing.  So the math goes.. if X = acclimation days,   X+X+Tourism days+1 to pack and leave.

snippet.textDisplay: Every time i would watch these videos i would get a lot of jealousy. Jealousy to live in a world where you can do what you want and go anywhere and still survive and have fall backs. Jealous of the man for having an amazing woman.. Jealous of her having a man she actually wants. Then the baby came along and im no longer jealous, just sad.  No one will read this comment because its days late....But i feel for this as i feel for my friends and family. I felt part of the ride with them, a journey of friendship and love and exploration... Then one, two, three, had children and the adventure for all of us stopped. They all left and were concerned about themselves and their family, rather than their extended family. I dont have a child and it probably feels amazing. But i miss my cousins and my really close friends doing things together as a group. I think that time is gone, the family time is here. This channel is now here... it will have a bunch of viewers because a bunch of their audience are having kids at the same time. Its just the adventure and commodore amongst adults will never be anymore, and I am full of sorrow because of that. Kids are a necessity but their birth is a death into something else... A love for the extended friends dies and wont ever be the same.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hello, hello and hello Elayna & Riley!


We're currently living in a van, travelling around New Zealand, loving every minute of it. Just like you, a question we've been asking ourselves lately is - what's the perfect amount of time to spend in a place?


We've been dotting about freedom camping spots every couple of days for the last 2 months or so. But now we're about to enter a new chapter of this adventure, staying relatively stationary as we've picked up some work on an apple orchard. Both of us are interested to try van life in this context.


Basically, we have no idea what's the perfect amount of time to stay in one place. We reckon it's just as long as your happy there, and the location is bringing the right values to your life at the time.


Love the videos and have done for a long time :)


J&C x
